properties.Title: Winter Storm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: An intense winter storm system will bring very strong winds as well as snow and blowing snow to Iqaluit and Kimmirut. Very strong winds with gusts to 90 km/h will weaken this morning. Snow will continue to accumulate today and Sunday evening giving a total of 10 to 20 cm. Blowing snow with poor visibilities at times is expected this morning and again on Monday. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Winter storm warnings are issued when multiple types of severe winter weather are expected to occur together. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

Area: Iqaluit, Kimmirut

properties.Title: Winter Storm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A potent winter storm will affect Baffin Island over the next few days. Strong northwesterly winds of 70 gusting to 90 km/h are expected to develop over Clyde River overnight Sunday into Monday morning. Snow and blowing snow are expected to reduce visibilities and possibly create blizzard conditions for Clyde River. Conditions will improve late on Monday. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Summary:
